---

## âœ… 1. Install Hugo

### On macOS:

```bash
brew install hugo
```

### On Linux:

```bash
sudo apt install hugo
```

### On Windows (using Chocolatey):

```bash
choco install hugo -confirm
```

Confirm it's working:

```bash
hugo version
```

---

## âœ… 2. Create a New Hugo Site

```bash
hugo new site curevia
cd curevia
```

---

## âœ… 3. Set Up Your Custom Layout

### Create the folder structure:

```bash
mkdir -p layouts
mkdir -p static/css static/images
```

### Add your files:

* ðŸ”¹ Your HTML â†’ `layouts/index.html`
* ðŸ”¹ Your CSS â†’ `static/css/style.css`
* ðŸ”¹ Your logo â†’ `static/images/logo.png`
* ðŸ”¹ Optional hero image â†’ `static/images/hero-bg.jpg`

> ðŸ’¡ You donâ€™t need a theme since you're using custom layout.

---

## âœ… 4. Add Sample Content

Create one post:

```bash
hugo new posts/welcome.md
```

Edit `content/posts/welcome.md` and write something simple:

```markdown
---
title: "Welcome to Curevia"
date: 2025-06-30
---

We're building the future of valve therapies.
```

---

## âœ… 5. Run the Hugo Server

```bash
hugo server
```

Visit: [http://localhost:1313](http://localhost:1313)

---

## âœ… 6. Modify Content

* **Homepage layout**: `layouts/index.html`
* **Styling**: `static/css/style.css`
* **Blog posts**: create `.md` files in `content/posts/`

---

## âœ… 7. Build for Production

```bash
hugo
```

The static site will be in `public/`.

You can deploy this folder to:

* Netlify
* GitHub Pages
* Vercel
* Surge
* Your server

